\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 For the Red Chile Oil:\
Combine all ingredients in a small {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} over low heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let oil infuse for 30 minutes. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Strain}} oil into a bowl.\
For the Shrimp:\
Preheat oven to 450 degrees F.\
Place the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/shrimp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 shrimp}} in a large oven {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/proof/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 proof}} casserole ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cazuela/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cazuela}}), pour the red chile oil over them and season the shrimp with the ancho chili powder and salt. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/roast/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Roast}} in the oven until pink and just cooked through, about 4 to 5 minutes for small shrimp, 6 to 7 minutes for medium.\
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with the chopped thyme. Serve immediately\cf2 .\cf0 \
